The paper deals with scheduling and multiuser multi-antenna transmission in cellular systems, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The use of game theory in the framework suggests a possible category of game theory and economics (cs.GT). The use of stochastic optimization techniques suggests a possible category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the mention of adaptive variable-rate coding and Hybrid ARQ suggests a possible category of multimedia (cs.MM).
